<h1>How a Simple Google Search Console Setup Sparked Massive Growth</h1>

<p>In Nairobi, a small e-commerce shop was struggling to get traffic despite having great products. They didn’t know which pages were performing well or which keywords were bringing in visitors. The game-changer? Setting up Google Search Console (GSC).</p>

<h2>Why Google Search Console Matters</h2>

<p>Google Search Console is a free tool that provides insights into how Google sees your website. It helps you:</p>
<ul>
<li>Track keyword performance</li>
<li>Identify indexing issues</li>
<li>Spot crawl errors</li>
<li>Understand user behavior via search queries</li>
<li>Enhance overall SEO strategy</li>
</ul>

<h2>Step 1: Verify Your Website</h2>

<p>They verified their website using multiple methods:</p>
<ul>
<li>HTML tag method</li>
<li>Google Analytics verification</li>
<li>Domain provider verification</li>
</ul>

<p>Once verified, GSC immediately started showing insights about their site performance.</p>

<h2>Step 2: Submit a Sitemap</h2>

<p>The e-commerce store submitted an XML sitemap to GSC. This helped Google find all pages and index them quickly.</p>

<p>👉 Related: <a href="https://dkdigitalseo.online/blog/xml-sitemap-seo-kenya-guide.html">XML Sitemap SEO Kenya Guide</a></p>

<h2>Step 3: Analyze Performance Reports</h2>

<p>They tracked:</p>
<ul>
<li>Total clicks and impressions</li>
<li>Click-through rates (CTR)</li>
<li>Keywords driving traffic</li>
<li>Pages with highest engagement</li>
</ul>

<p>Insights revealed underperforming pages and untapped keyword opportunities.</p>

<h2>Step 4: Fix Indexing & Crawl Errors</h2>

<p>GSC identified:</p>
<ul>
<li>Broken pages (404 errors)</li>
<li>Blocked pages due to robots.txt</li>
<li>Redirect errors</li>
</ul>

<p>Fixing these issues improved rankings and user experience.</p>

<h2>Step 5: Optimize Content Based on Queries</h2>

<p>Using the search queries report, the store optimized meta titles, descriptions, and content for keywords that were driving impressions but low CTR.</p>

<p>👉 Related reading: <a href="https://dkdigitalseo.online/blog/seo-content-writing-kenya-case-study.html">SEO Content Writing Kenya Case Study</a></p>

<h2>Step 6: Track Enhancements & Rich Results</h2>

<p>GSC allowed them to track:</p>
<ul>
<li>Structured data errors (schema)</li>
<li>Mobile usability issues</li>
<li>Core Web Vitals improvements</li>
</ul>

